- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the decidability of infinite games, which is a topic closely related to logic.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses games and winning strategies.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with coordination among players, which is a common topic in AI research.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper discusses complexity bounds for the strategy synthesis problem.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with $\omega$-regular winning conditions given by parity automata, which is a topic related to discrete mathematics.
